Product Version     25.10    Cadence Design Systems, Inc.
deselectSecondaryPGNet(25.10)                    deselectSecondaryPGNet(25.10)

Name
       deselectSecondaryPGNet - Deselects Power/Ground (P/G) net wire segments
       from specified instances

Syntax
       deselectSecondaryPGNet

       [-help]

       -insts <inst>+

       -net <net>

       Deselects  Power/Ground  (P/G)  net  wire  segments  from specified in-
       stances. This command provides an easy way to deselect the routing from
       specific instance P/G pins to stripes.

       Note: This command does not support dangling secondary P/G nets.

Parameters
       -help  Prints the usage of the command. For a detailed  description  of
              the command, use the man command:

              man deselectSecondaryPGNet

       -insts <inst>+
              Specifies  the  list  of instances that have a secondary PG pin.
              Wildcards are supported in instance names.

              If one or more specified instances does  not  connect  with  the
              specified net, the tool displays a warning and ignores those in-
              stances.

       -net <net_name>
              Specifies the net name.

              Note: <net_name> does not take any wildcard values.

Examples
              *

                The  following command deselects the routing from the instance
                A P/G pin in net VDD_1 to the power stripe:

                deselectSecondaryPGNet -net VDD_1 -insts {A}

              *

                The following command deselects the routing from the P/G  pins
                in instances A and B in net VDD_1 to the power stripe:

                deselectSecondaryPGNet -net VDD_1 -insts {A B}

              *

                The  following command deselects the routing from the P/G pins
                in instances A/B1 and A/B2 in net VDD_1 to the power stripe:

                deselectSecondaryPGNet -net VDD_1 -insts {A/*}

